/* Copy new items into override: item >> override */
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqhead01.itm~ ~override/rqhead01.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Grothuk's Head~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Grothuk's Head~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This Gro'Thuk is one ugly Orc he looks more like a half-troll.~

/* Copy new items into override: item >> override */
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqcrat01.itm~ ~override/rqcrat01.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Large crate~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Large crate~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Large and heavy crate with lock on top. If you stop and listen closely you can hear muffled voices and movement. There must be someone inside!~

// Letter to Nemean
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletne1.itm~ ~override/rqletne1.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~<CHARNAME> has proved to an obstacle and obstacles can be removed if executed by capable man like yourself. Be steadfast, do not be deterred no matter what the cost.
Our old meeting places has become compromised meet me at Blade and Stars.~

// Nemeans journal
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqnemjou.itm~ ~override/rqnemjou.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Nemean's Journal~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Nemean's Journal~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~It seems this Nemean was quite a meticulous assassin, keeping a very detailed journal. The last few entries he wrote describe his latest assassination:
I took a contract from Alatos to assassinate a former Thieves Guild member, Krivy. It should be difficult, but I love the challenge.
Now I understand why Alatos hired me to kill Krivy t seems he is trying to get <CHARNAME> into power. If I killed <CHARNAME>, that would ruin Krivy's plans and force him out of the city, where my trackers could find him much more easily than in the urban squalor.
This Lerov is certainly annoying, but I still need him since he's working for us. However, if an opportunity arises to kill him, I won't hesitate.
Lerov has been spinning tall tales again, but this time he blurted out that he actually prefers <CHARNAME> to live. I can't work with people of dubious loyalty, so I'll have to dispose of him.
Damn this skulking around! I was nearly captured by the Flaming Fist! Worse, they know who I am and are actively hunting me. Looks like I'll have to speak to Lezgyn Hawk about this.
Talking with Lezgyn Hawk was useless as always though he did send Flemil to investigate.
Flemil said it was the Flaming Fist mercenary Trest who initiated a citywide manhunt for me. Perhaps I should send someone to find out how Fist learned my name and whereabouts.~

// letter
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletkr1.itm~ ~override/rqletkr1.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Krivy's contact list~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Krivy's contact list~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Talvin of Gelfiven Drakon Tavern, Central Baldur's Gate

Gemerkan Keexie Tavern, East Baldur's Gate

Melwis Blade and Stars, Southeast Baldur's Gate

Gvalas Three Old Kegs, North Baldur's Gate

Temur of Droliegen Blushing Mermaid, Northeast Baldur's Gate

Turpin of Milgerin, Ivylla Donnerstrom, Remelsen: All three are in Splurging Sturgeon, Northeast Baldur's Gate

Nestor Low Lantern, South Baldur's Gate

Ioviis Elfsong Tavern 2nd floor, East Baldur's Gate~

COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletkr2.itm~ ~override/rqletkr2.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Krivy's letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Krivy's letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~<CHARNAME> i am writing to you in great haste. Our "friend" Lezgyn must have betrayed us thus i am no longer in Baldur's Gate you can try to get revenge on our main enemy the Thieves Guild who were behind all attempts on your life but i would just recommend you to leave the city. No doubt that this will escalate and Thieves will send even more assassin after you.~

COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletbe1.itm~ ~override/rqletbe1.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Ducal Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Ducal Letter~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~You see parchment with wax seal of city of Baldur's Gate and Belts personal seal.

Dear <CHARNAME> you have saved us from vile Sarevok though your valiant actions against your brother do not allow you destabilize our city in these dangerous times. We are aware of your allegiance to Krivy and we advise you to cease and desist any further cooperation with him. Know that Krivy used to work for Alatos. Now i am not unreasonable man you can if you wish cooperate with me. We could use one so resourceful speak if you are ready to switch to side of good and order speak to my servant Alvier in Ducal Palace.

Duke Belt~

// Letter of credence
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletre3.itm~ ~override/rqletre3.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Letter of credence~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Letter of credence~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Letter of Credence

I, Agraar Kelthor, do hereby appoint and authorize Melwis of Baldur's Gate to act on my behalf. This authorization is temporary and grants Melwis the authority to represent me in all relevant matters during this period.

Signed,
Agraar Kelthor

This is lavishly decorated letter with signature and wax seal at the bottom serves as identification that bearer of this letter is representing Kelthor Family. As far as you can tell this is the real deal and you can trust bearer of this letter is acting on behalf of who he says he is.~

