COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqletmal.itm~ ~override/rqletmal.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Malzoths Letter~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Malzoths Letter~
SAY DESC
~You must apologize me for not wanting to meet and sending my just my familiar to deliver your reward but i had other pressing matters to attend to. Utilize your new tools well.

Malzoth~

// Potion of Storm Giant Strength
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqpotn61.itm~ ~override/rqpotn61.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Potion of Storm Giant Strength~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Potion of Storm Giant Strength~
SAY DESC
~Potion of Storm Giant Strength
When a giant strength potion is consumed, the individual gains great strength and bonuses to hit and damage while using any hand-held or thrown weapon.  The effect lasts for 10 turns.

This potion was modified so that even non warriors could use it to enhance their strength.

STATISTICS:

Strength:  24  (Storm Giant Strength)
~

// New items ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Belt of Freedom -------------------- 1
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqbelt03.itm~ ~override/rqbelt03.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Belt~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Belt of Freedom~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC

~Girdles are generally similar to belts.  Unlike belts, girdles are not used to hold up pants and dungarees, but to carry pouches, scabbards, and the like.

STATISTICS:

Weight:  2~

SAY DESC
~Belt of Freedom was invented by illustrious thief named Helget. Helget needed protection from magical ensnarement but did not wanted to be obvious by acquiring Ring of Free Action so he had enchanted his belt. Since then belt has changed hands multiple times mostly through violence. The only question unanswered in your mind is whether this Helget wants his belt back.

STATISTICS:

Special:  The wearer is immune to everything,  magical and otherwise,  that affects mobility in any way.  This includes haste and slow spells.

Not Usable By:
  Wizardslayer~

// Belt of Vigor and Wisdom -------------------- 2
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqbelt04.itm~ ~override/rqbelt04.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Belt~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Belt of Vigor and Wisdom~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC

~Girdles are generally similar to belts.  Unlike belts, girdles are not used to hold up pants and dungarees, but to carry pouches, scabbards, and the like.

STATISTICS:

Weight:  2~

SAY DESC
~Belt of Vigor and Wisdom
The reasoning behind placing enchantments that enhance users' Wisdom Dexterity and Constitution is not known, though scholars have two competing theories. One theory proposed by Scholar Amarannath speculates that the belt was intended for the Cult of Shar located in Tethyr. They point to the belt's unusual craftsmanship which is typical for Tethyr. The War Wizards of Cormyr on the other hand suggest that the enchantment runes tend to be found on enchanted items from makers residing in Waterdeep.

Whatever the case, one of these belts was worn by a priest of Tempus who was instrumental in the war against goblin tribes in DR1247. An army led by an unknown priest of Tempus was eventually defeated, and the belt appeared in the possession of a priestess of Auril named Joralia. Records indicate she lived to an advanced age, so it is assumed that the belt was in her possession when she died.

The last known wielder was a fighter named Belgeron from Waterdeep, who bought this belt at an auction in the city. Belgeron was involved in a coup against the rulers of Waterdeep; he and other plotters sought to place his men in various influential leadership positions in the city. However, his plot was discovered, and he had to flee.

It is not known how many of these belts still survive, but there must be more than one in Faerun. Both Amarannath and the War Wizards of Cormyr agree on this point.

STATISTICS:

STATISTICS:
Wight: 2 lbs

STATISTICS:
Dexterity +1
Constitution +1
Wisdom +1

Not Usable By:
  Wizardslayer~

// Veilguard -------------------- 3
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqbelt05.itm~ ~override/rqbelt05.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Magical Rope~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Veilguard~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC

~On first glance, the appearance of this rope might fool peasants or village merchants into discarding it as an ordinary rope, but any adventurer will recognize its aura of potent protective magic.

STATISTICS:

Weight:  5 lbs~

SAY DESC
~Veilguard is one of the stranger items in Faerun instead of having appearance of belt whoever enchanted it chose to enchant an ordinary rope instead of more practical belt or girdle. Scholars are unsure who exactly crafted this girdle disguised at rope but its protective qualities are undeniable. Only entry describing Veilguard comes from Athkatlan Priest who found following letter just by accident.
Enclosed you will find the rope, as discussed.  When worn around the waist, this rope will cloak the wearer in an invisible, non-encumbering armor.  Its protective qualities are equivalent to a full suit of plate armor, shielding you from harm.
Furthermore, tying the rope around your waist will enhance your fortune.
There is no other indication of its origin other than purple colored threads woven into rope which could indicate Sharran origin.

STATISTICS:
Wight: 5 lbs

STATISTICS:
Luck +2
Armor Class: 1

Not Usable By:
  Wizardslayer~

// Boots of harder road -------------------- 4
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqboot05.itm~ ~override/rqboot05.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Boots~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Boots of Hard Road~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC

~Boots are normally hand-made by cobblers.  Common boots are made by using a form, but good boots are designed for the foot of an individual.

STATISTICS:

Weight:  4~

SAY DESC
~Boots of Hard Road
Apparently these boots were enchanted by Elvigar who was commander of small militia located in Cormyr. Further records state that some of boots have were either stolen from militias armory or looted by victorious hobgoblins after successful ambush made by Tuk tribe in DR1279. Since then several pairs appeared in Sword Coast.

STATISTICS:

AC bonus +1
Weight: 4
+10 % bonus to hit points

Not Usable By:
  Druid
  Fighter/Druid~

// Engel's Bracers -------------------- 5
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqbrac04.itm~ ~override/rqbrac04.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Bracers~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Engel's Bracers~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Bracers are thick bands of metal or leather that are strapped, belted, or tied to a character's forearm.~

SAY DESC
~Engel's Bracers
Creation of pairs these bracers is attributed to Engel from Rasheman. Engel used to be mage of power however after particularly disastrous teleport spell accident. From then on he refused ever to use magic to transport himself but found traveling exhausting and this is why these braces came into existence. This is supposed to be creation myth of Engel's bracers but chroniclers might have confused this myth with other myth because bracers do enhance bearers dexterity more that constitution.

STATISTICS:
Wight: 1 lbs

STATISTICS:
Dexterity +2
Constitution +1

Unusable By:
Wizardslayer~

// Ghosts Punch -------------------- 6
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqstaf01.itm~ ~override/rqstaf01.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Quarterstaff~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Ghosts Punch~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~The simplest and humblest of staff weapons, the quarterstaff is a length of wood ranging six to nine feet in length.  High-quality quarterstaves are made of stout oak and are shod with metal at both ends.  The quarterstaff must be wielded with both hands.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1D6
Damage type:  crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Staff
Type:  2-handed
Requires: 5 Strength~

SAY DESC
~Ghosts Punch
Creation of this staff is attributed to Fighter Mage Khornovus who was chief of militia training for the city of Akanax. He wanted a weapon for disciplining his pupils if need arose. Which in city like Akanax as trainer for its militia had plenty of opportunities to use this staff. Story how sfaff left left Khornovus possession is interesting one. One of trainees had enough of Khornovus *disciplining* and conspired with other trainees steal his master staff of spare himself of beating. The story goes that one night group of trainees and stole Khornovus staff however mage found about the theft. Unable to withstand Khornovus interrogation students procured ordinary enchanted staff and pretended to be hit when they were *hit* by Khornovus swings by counterfeit staff. Since disappearance of Ghosts Punch from history scholars record only one similar weapon, Phantom Staff to have similar ability to strike from afar with supposedly melee weapon.

STATISTICS:
Damage:  1D6 + 1
THAC0:  +1
Damage type:  crushing
Weight: 4
Speed Factor: 3
Range (feet): 30
Proficiency Type: Staff
Type:  2-handed
Requires: 5 Strength~



