// Wand of Cures -------------------- 13
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqwand02.itm~ ~override/rqwand02.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Wand~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Wand of Cures~

SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Wands are 1 1/4 feet long and slender.  They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something - metal, crystal, stone, etc.  They are fragile and tend to break easily.  Because of this, they are often kept in cases.

Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item).  When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.~

SAY DESC
~Wand of Cures
Priests typically create less wands than mages exception to this rule are typically priests of Waukeen and so it is how this wand came into being. One of larger monasteries that Waukeenar clergy produced wands were located in Vast near city Procampur and this wand bear identification mark indicating it was produced there. Such marking are unreliable though as these marks are widely falsified and wand with falsified marks are typically of lesser quality.

STATISTICS:

Ability 1:

Neutralize Poison (Necromancy)
Range: Touch
Duration: Instant
Area of Effect: Creature touched
Saving Throw: None

This spell removes all toxins from the body, both natural and magical in nature.  When this spell is cast upon a poisoned individual, it immediately neutralizes any poison and restores 10 lost hit points. This spell will also cure any diseases that the target may be suffering from, as well as blindness and deafness.


Ability 2:

Remove Paralysis (Abjuration)
Range (feet): 150
Duration: Permanent
Area of Effect: 20 ft radius
Saving Throw: None

By the use of this spell, the priest can free several creatures from the effects of any paralyzation or related magic (such as a ghoul touch, or a hold spell).

Ability 3:

Lesser Restoration (Necromancy)
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, the life-energy level of the recipient is raised.  This reverses any previous life-energy-level drain of the creature by a force or monster.  The casting of this spell is very draining on the priest and she will likely require rest immediately after the casting, as it will cause days worth of fatigue almost instantaneously.

Usable By:
Clerics(Single-class,Multi-class,Dual-class)
~

// Wand of Entsele's Warding Glyph --------------------
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqwand03.itm~ ~override/rqwand03.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Wand~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Entsele's Warding Glyph~

SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~Wands are 1 1/4 feet long and slender.  They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something - metal, crystal, stone, etc.  They are fragile and tend to break easily.  Because of this, they are often kept in cases.

Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item).  When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.~

SAY DESC
~Entsele's Warding Glyph
Entsele was a mage who belonged to brigand band setup to preyed on peasants traveller and even on other brigand bands in east Moonsea and due Entsele being only mage he assumed leadership after brief struggle with previous leader and after attaining mantle of leadership had this wand made to help in his ambushes. Wand was thought to be lost but then it reappeared in Sword Coast in hands of bandits which caused the Iron Crisis. There is no indication where it was made though it it likely the wand is manufactured by spell component guild and custom enchantment was put by unknown enchanter.

A Entsele's Warding Glyph is a powerful inscription magically drawn to prevent unauthorized or hostile creatures from passing, entering, or opening. It can be used to guard a small bridge, to ward an entry, or as a trap on a chest or box.
Any creature violating the warded area is subject to the magic it stores. A successful saving throw vs. spell enables the creature to escape half of damage of the glyph.  Multiple glyphs cannot be cast on the same area; although if a cabinet had three drawers, each could be separately warded.
When the spell is cast, the user weaves a tracery of faintly glowing lines around the warding sigil.  When the glyph is activated, it deals 12d8. Creatures failing their saving throws each suffer full damage from the blast. Those who roll successful saving throws manage to dodge, fall flat, or roll aside, each receiving half damage thus 6d8.

Level: 7
Range: Visual range of caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 12-foot radius
Saving Throw: 1/2

Not usable by:
 Fighter
 Cleric
 Druid
 Thief
 Paladin
 Ranger
~

// Initiate ring -------------------- 14
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqring05.itm~ ~override/rqring05.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Ring~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Initiate Ring~
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~A ring is a small band of precious metal that is used as jewelry.  Some rare rings have had enchantments placed upon them that confer various magical abilities.  These rings are highly sought after, especially by those of the adventuring profession.~
SAY DESC
~Initiate ring
This ring was enchanted for monastery of Sun Soul monks Tasseldale and it was sometimes given to initiates who were sent for extremely dangerous missions for monastery. Chroniclers records only one such episode when monk named Orgolin who was sent to aid militia of Moontassel to defeat Ironarm tribe of Hobgoblins who besieged the city to break the siege Orgolin and his men were sent on surprise attack on tent of an Gnoll chieftain. Attack succeeded though at cost of all monks lives except youngest monk Orgolin who returned to monastery with this ring. Leaderless gnolls were dispersed by simultaneous attack from city Cavalry.

STATISTICS:
Magic Resistance:  +10% Bonus
Equipped Ability: Increases movement rate
Equipped Abilities: Wearer regenerates 1 hit point every 3 seconds

Not Usable By:
Wizardslayer
~

