  Damage: 8d6 (save vs. wands for half)
  Range: 100 ft
  Area: One creature~

// Nebula Adapatio   --------------------
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqmisc04.itm~ ~override/rqmisc04.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Hourglass~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Nebula Adapatio~

SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This instrument, made of two bulbs of glass joined by a narrow passage, tells time with a portion of sand that falls between the two bulbs. Hour glasses are a common time telling device throughout the Realms.~

SAY DESC
~Nebula Adapatio
No one knows how this artifact came into existence, but if its similarity to Horologium timekeeping devices is any indication, it supports the War Wizards of Cormyr theory about a guild specializing in crafting charged magic artifacts. However, this hourglass is significantly more potent. Not only can it spawn a horrible acid fog, but it also allows the caster to choose who is affected and who is attacked by the acid, making this artifact much more useful for adventuring groups who value not harming their members or being hit by the fog. The latest writings about Nebula Adapatio by an unknown War Wizard who examined the artifact were astonished by its targeting capability of the acid, but they were unable to understand how exactly this ability was achieved without destroying the artifact. How exactly this artifact came into the possession of the drow who gave it to you is truly a mystery.

STATISTICS:
  Special Abilities (thrice per day): Can cast acidic fog centered on user to harm his enemies.
  Nebula Adapatio (Evocation)
  Level: 8
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
  Saving Throw: None

The casting of a Nebula Adapatio spell creates an area of solid fog that has the additional property of being highly acidic. All enemies of the caster not immune to acid must roll a saving throw against breath weapons or suffer 12d8 points of damage if failing or 6d8 points of damage if succeeding for each round they are exposed to the vapors of the death fog.

Not usable by:
 Fighter
 Cleric
 Druid
 Thief
 Paladin
 Ranger
~

// Horologium Debilitas --------------------
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqmisc05.itm~ ~override/rqmisc05.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Hourglass~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Horologium Debilitas~

SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~This instrument, made of two bulbs of glass joined by a narrow passage, tells time with a portion of sand that falls between the two bulbs. Hour glasses are a common time telling device throughout the Realms.~

SAY DESC
~Horologium Debilitas
Yet another timekeeping device confirms the War Wizards of Cormyr theory about an old lost manufacturing guild for charged artifacts. This hourglass has "Merkahart" written on both the bottom and the top bulb cover. It is possible that Merkahart is the name of a long-lost guild, though no such marking is found on other hourglass artifacts.

Regardless of its origins, this powerful artifact can cast a debilitating curse on your opponent.

STATISTICS:

Energy Drain (Necromancy)

Level: 9
Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Target Creature
Saving Throw: None
The casting of this spell opens a channel between the caster's plane and the Negative Energy plane. The caster acts as a conduit between the two planes, sucking life from a victim and transferring it to the Negative Energy plane, draining the victim of 5 levels of experience. The target loses levels, Hit Dice, hit points, and abilities permanently. These levels can only be restored by a priest's restoration spell.

Another effect of this artifact is that the victim will be enfeebled thus less strong, less agile, and less tough, with a reduction of 3 points in all mentioned attributes. This effect is not permanent and lasts for one turn.

Not usable by:
 Fighter
 Cleric
 Druid
 Thief
 Paladin
 Ranger
~

// Demnar's Failure ------------------------------ 26
COPY ~grand_duke/itm/rqdart01.itm~ ~override/rqdart01.itm~
/* Unidentified name */
SAY NAME1 ~Dart~
/* Identified name */
SAY NAME2 ~Demnar's Failure +4~

SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC
~The dart is a small, easily concealable missile weapon that is thrown rather than fired from a bow or other launcher.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1D3
Damage type:  missile (piercing)
Weight: 0
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Dart
Type:  1-handed
Not Usable By:
 Cleric~

SAY DESC
~Demnar's Failure
The history of Demnar's failed dart is not very clear, but historians link it to the siege of the city Hlath, which is undated but probably occurred around the 12th century DR. This powerful dart was made by blacksmith Eregiel and enchanted by mage Dezgyn Lefthanded, who sent a band of adventurers to either kill or bribe the captain of a crucial part of the besieging army. Since no one has mentioned this dart afterwards, it must have been lost during an expedition by the adventurers. Chroniclers assume that it was most likely lost during a fire that broke out in the earthworks built by the besieging army. While most scholars think that the current name of this dart comes from a failed adventurers foray, this is not true. Demnar's intention was to create an even more powerful version that would strike with all four elements, and yes, the resulting weapon does strike with four different types of damage, but they are mixed up: instead of acid, it strikes with poison; instead of cold, it strikes with pure magical damage. Therefore, Demnar regarded his order as a failure.

STATISTICS:

THAC0:  +4 bonus
Damage:  1D3 +4, +1d2 fire damage, +1d2 magic damage, +1d2 electric damage, +1d2 poison damage
Damage type:  missile (piercing)
Weight: 0
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: Dart
Type:  1-handed
Not Usable By:
 Cleric~



